description: a(n) = sum_{d|n, n/d=1 mod 4} d^3 - sum_{d|n, n/d=3 mod 4} d^3.
comments: Multiplicative because it is the Dirichlet convolution of A000578 = n^3 and A101455 = [1 0 -1 0 1 0 -1 ...], which are both multiplicative. - _Christian G. Bower_, May 17 2005
mathematica: max = 40; s = Sum[n^3*x^(n-1)/(1+x^(2*n)), {n, 1, max}] + O[x]^max; CoefficientList[s, x] (* _Jean-Fran√ßois Alcover_, Dec 02 2015, after _Vladeta Jovovic_ *)
prog: (PARI) a(n) = sumdiv(n, d, d^3*(((n/d) % 4)==1)) - sumdiv(n, d, d^3*(((n/d) % 4)==3)); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Feb 16 2015
